# Spark Frosted Conversation Workspace™ (Spec 109)

**Full document:** `docs/SPARK_FROSTED_CONVERSATION_WORKSPACE_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Conversation stack:** Spec 105–108 · **Layout:** `.cursor/rules/workspace-layout.mdc`

## Primary rule

**The user should always know what to do next.**

## Core idea

One centered frosted-glass conversation panel. Room visible around edges. Not a dashboard. Not three columns.

Implementation: `companion-workspace-frosted` · `workspaceFloatingCardShellClass()` in `lib/workspaceLayoutTokens.ts`

## Typography minimums (desktop)

| Element | px |
|---------|-----|
| Shari message | 30–36 |
| User message | 26–30 |
| Buttons / input | 24–30 |
| Supporting | 22–24 |

No pale gray on glass. No thin fonts.

## Six workspace states

1. **Conversation** — default; one exchange visible
2. **Help Options** — stuck triggers; four numbered choices
3. **Research** — in-panel; 3–5 findings; same frosted surface
4. **Draft Ready** — permission before show
5. **Review** — draft primary; chat fades; old chat not behind draft
6. **Completion** — only true prepared items; permission to review/save

**Types:** `SparkFrostedWorkspaceState` in `lib/sparkFrostedConversationWorkspace/types.ts`

## Non-negotiables

- One question at a time
- Numbered choices when helpful
- **Input always visible** — never hidden when choices shown
- No scroll chasing — next message in view
- Permission before save/export/publish/send/delete

## Map

Folded map bottom-right — pauses conversation, never destroys it.

## Mobile

One column · large text · input fixed bottom · mic always available · choices stacked

## Before shipping conversational UI

- [ ] Primary rule — next step obvious?
- [ ] Typography meets minimums?
- [ ] Input always visible?
- [ ] Review state hides competing chat?
- [ ] Same behavior in every room (Spec 108)?
- [ ] Permission before destructive/export actions?

